 \"page-0250.md\")\n    b.ReportAllocs()\n    b.ResetTimer()\n    for iteration := 0; iteration < b.N; iteration++ {\n        target := \"asset-a.bin\"\n        if iteration%2 == 1 { target = \"asset-b.bin\" }\n        content := fmt.Sprintf(\"# Changed\\n\\n[target](../%s)\\n\", target)\n        if err := os.WriteFile(changedPath, []byte(content), 0o644); err != nil { b.Fatal(err) }\n        plan, err := Reconcile(root)\n        if err != nil { b.Fatal(err) }\n        if _, err := ApplyAndSave(&plan); err != nil { b.Fatal(err) }\n    }\n}\n\nfunc createBenchmarkRepository(tb testing.TB, root string, count int) { /* creates docs/page-N.md linking to asset-a.bin */ }\n```\n\ninternal/links/reconcile.go begins:\n```go\nfunc Reconcile(repositoryRoot string) (Plan, error) {\n    root, err := filepath.Abs(repositoryRoot)\n    if err != nil { return Plan{}, err }\n    previousFiles, previousLinks, initialized, err := loadState(root)\n    if err != nil { return Plan{}, err }\n    inventory, err := buildInventory(root, previousFiles)\n    if err != nil { return Plan{}, err }\n    plan := Plan{RepositoryRoot: filepath.Clean(root), Initialized: initialized, NeedsInitialization: !initialized, Files: inventory.manifest, Links: LinksManifest{SchemaVersion: schemaVersion}}\n    if !initialized { plan.Messages = append(plan.Messages, \"Link state is not initialized; this pass records a baseline and does not repair links.\") }\n    previousBySource := previousLinkIndex(previousLinks)\n    previousByID := fileRecordIndex(previousFiles)\n    currentByID := fileRecordIndex(inventory.manifest)\n    internal, err := buildInternalMoveRewrites(root, previousBySource, previousByID, currentByID)\n    if err != nil { return Plan{}, err }\n    for _, source := range markdownSources(inventory) {\n        if rewrite, ok := internal[source.record.ID]; ok {\n            plan.Rewrites = append(plan.Rewrites, rewrite.rewrite)\n            plan.Updates = append(plan.Updates, rewrite.update)\n            plan.Links.Links = append(plan.Links.Links, rewrite.records...)\n            plan.Messages = append(plan.Messages, rewrite.messages...)\n            continue\n        }\n        previousSource := previousByID[source.record.ID]\n        previousRecords := previousBySource[source.record.ID]\n        if initialized && sourceUnchanged(previousSource, source.record) && recordsReusable(previousRecords) {\n            for _, record := range previousRecords {\n                record.SourcePath = source.record.Path\n                plan.Links.Links = append(plan.Links.Links, record)\n            }\n            continue\n        }\n        if err := reconcileMarkdownSource(&plan, inventory, source, previousRecords, initialized); err != nil { return Plan{}, err }\n    }\n    plan.Files = inventory.manifest\n    sortManifests(&plan.Files, &plan.Links)\n    return plan, nil\n}\n```\n\ninternal/links/apply.go begins:\n```go\nfunc ApplyAndSave(plan *Plan) (int, error) {\n    suppressions, err := ApplyGenerated(plan.Rewrites)\n    if err != nil { return 0, err }\n    plan.Suppressions = suppressions\n    if err := refreshGeneratedSources(plan); err != nil { return 0, err }\n    if err := Save(*plan); err != nil { return 0, err }\n    return len(plan.Rewrites), nil\n}\n```\n\ninternal/links/state.go:\n- loadState(root) opens/reads the private .ddocs go-git repository.\n- Save(plan) prepares desired records and publishes them through repository.Transaction(...).\n\ninternal/links/inventory.go:\n- buildInventory(root, previous) scans the tree, hashes changed files, and preserves identities.\n\nDesired implementation:\n1. Preserve public production behavior. Add internal profiled helpers, with existing Reconcile and ApplyAndSave as thin wrappers.\n2. Add timing value types with time.Duration fields and String methods. Reconcile phases: state load/open, inventory build, planning/reconciliation, total. Apply phases: generated filesystem rewrite application, generated-source refresh/verification, .ddocs state publication, total.\n3. Timings must be populated on successful operations. Avoid global state and application logging.\n4. Update both benchmarks to accumulate phase durations and expose average phase metrics via b.ReportMetric. Keep normal benchmark ns/op and allocations.\n5. Add deterministic tests that assert phase totals/order/invariants without upper performance thresholds. Use sufficiently nontrivial synthetic repositories.\n6. Add an opt-in external fixture integration test gated by `DDOCS_LINK_TIMING_FIXTURE`. It must copy the fixture into t.TempDir(), including `.ddocs`, never mutate the original, run a baseline, identify the repository file with the highest number of inbound links, rename it inside the copy, time reconciliation and apply, assert at least one rewrite, verify an idempotent follow-up has zero rewrites, and log readable timing summaries with t.Logf. Skip symlinks and hard-coded always-ignored traversal dirs as normal traversal would. A simple private copy helper in the test is acceptable.\n7. Do not add hard timing thresholds.\n8. Keep files reasonably small. A new `internal/links/timing.go` and `internal/links/timing_test.go` are acceptable.\n\nReturn:\n- exact complete contents for timing.go and timing_test.go;\n- exact complete replacement contents for benchmark_test.go;\n- precise minimal edits for reconcile.go and apply.go, quoting exact old/new blocks.\n- identify any correctness concern in the requested external-fixture algorithm.","prompt_chars":6658,"result":{"exit_code":0,"exit_signal":null,"timed_out":false,"error":null,"turn_status":"completed","final_message":"Below is the implementation plan and proposed patches. The supplied excerpts omit the complete current function bodies, imports, and the inventory traversal ignore list, so the `reconcile.go`/`apply.go` edits are keyed minimal edits rather than full-file replacements.\n\n## Implementation plan\n\n1. Add `ReconcileTimings` and `ApplyTimings` in `internal/links/timing.go`.\n2. Move current reconciliation/application bodies into unexported helpers that accept timing sinks.\n3. Keep `Reconcile` and `ApplyAndSave` behaviorally identical wrappers.\n4. Update benchmarks to use profiled helpers and report average phase durations.\n5. Add deterministic synthetic-tree timing/idempotence tests.\n6. Add an opt-in fixture test using `DDOCS_LINK_TIMING_FIXTURE`.\n7. Run:\n\n```text\ngofmt -w internal/links/*.go\ngo test -count=1 ./...\ngo vet ./...\ngo build ./...\ngit diff --check\ngit commit -m \"test: add link updater phase timing coverage\"\n```\n\n## New file: `internal/links/timing.go`\n\n```go\npackage links\n\nimport (\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"time\"\n)\n\n// ReconcileTimings records the major phases of a reconciliation pass.\ntype ReconcileTimings struct {\n\tStateLoad      time.Duration\n\tInventoryBuild time.Duration\n\tPlanning       time.Duration\n\tTotal          time.Duration\n}\n\nfunc (t ReconcileTimings) String() string {\n\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\n\t\t\"state-load=%s inventory-build=%s planning=%s total=%s\",\n\t\tt.StateLoad,\n\t\tt.InventoryBuild,\n\t\tt.Planning,\n\t\tt.Total,\n\t)\n}\n\n// ApplyTimings records the major phases of applying and persisting a plan.\ntype ApplyTimings struct {\n\tFilesystemRewrite     time.Duration\n\tGeneratedSourceRefresh time.Duration\n\tDdocsPublication      time.Duration\n\tTotal                 time.Duration\n}\n\nfunc (t ApplyTimings) String() string {\n\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\n\t\t\"filesystem-rewrite=%s generated-source-refresh=%s ddocs-publication=%s total=%s\",\n\t\tt.FilesystemRewrite,\n\t\tt.GeneratedSourceRefresh,\n\t\tt.DdocsPublication,\n\t\tt.Total,\n\t)\n}\n```\n\n## New file: `internal/links/timing_test.go`\n\n```go\npackage links\n\nimport (\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"io/fs\"\n\t\"net/url\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"path/filepath\"\n\t\"regexp\"\n\t\"sort\"\n\t\"strings\"\n\t\"testing\"\n\t\"time\"\n)\n\nfunc TestReconciliationAndApplicationTimings(t *testing.T) {\n\troot := t.TempDir()